zhac-components — Mixed-license component collection

This repository contains ten ESP-IDF components with a deliberate
mixed-license layout. Each component directory carries its own
authoritative `LICENSE` file, and every source file carries an
`SPDX-License-Identifier:` header.

| Component        | License              | SPDX                |
|------------------|----------------------|---------------------|
| zap_common       | Apache License 2.0   | Apache-2.0          |
| metrics          | Apache License 2.0   | Apache-2.0          |
| event_bus        | GNU AGPL v3 or later | AGPL-3.0-or-later   |
| hap_protocol     | GNU AGPL v3 or later | AGPL-3.0-or-later   |
| hap_session      | GNU AGPL v3 or later | AGPL-3.0-or-later   |
| hap_json         | GNU AGPL v3 or later | AGPL-3.0-or-later   |
| device_shadow    | GNU AGPL v3 or later | AGPL-3.0-or-later   |
| device_backend   | GNU AGPL v3 or later | AGPL-3.0-or-later   |
| zap_store        | GNU AGPL v3 or later | AGPL-3.0-or-later   |
| zhc_adapter      | GNU AGPL v3 or later | AGPL-3.0-or-later   |

Canonical license texts live in `LICENSES/`:

- `LICENSES/Apache-2.0.txt`
- `LICENSES/AGPL-3.0-or-later.txt`

Rationale for the split:

- `zap_common` + `metrics` are portable utilities reused by
  `embedded-zhc` (also Apache-2.0) and are valuable as a standalone
  library outside ZHAC. Keeping them permissive preserves that
  reusability.
- Everything else is tightly coupled to ZHAC's architecture
  (HAP wire format, device-shadow persistence, the ZHC bridge)
  and carries ZHAC's copyleft terms.

Compatibility: Apache-2.0 code can be combined with AGPL-3.0-or-later
code. A firmware build that links both Apache and AGPL components is
distributed as a combined work under AGPL-3.0-or-later. The Apache
components remain Apache-2.0 when used in isolation.

